 Project Overview 
This repository contains my Digital Literacy Portfolio, created for the CSE0001 Digital Literacy course[cite: 1, 2, 6]. As a Student Digital Ambassador, the goal of this project is to demonstrate how to navigate the digital world safely and professionally. The repository is organized into five tasks, each corresponding to a specific module from the course. 

 Module Summaries 

 Task 1: Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic (Module 1) 
 Summary: A visual resource created to help peers understand digital literacy, safe internet practices, and professional communication. 

 Task 2: Build Your Student Digital Portfolio (Module 2) 
 Summary: Establishing a foundational, professional digital presence across key platforms utilized by employers and the academic community. 

 Task 3: Explore Coding & Collaboration Platforms (Module 3) 
 Summary: Building familiarity with coding practice platforms and cloud collaboration tools to assist in studying and collaborating online. 

 Task 4: Draft a Professional Email & Etiquette Guide (Module 4) 
 Summary: Demonstrating the application of proper email etiquette and outlining clear rules for responsible social media use as a college student.

 Task 5: Cybercrime Awareness Case Study & Prevention Guide (Module 5) 
 Summary: Researching a realistic cybercrime scenario to produce an awareness resource, alongside an actionable prevention checklist for online safety. 

